other_tests.findings: Appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring 10 mm, with a moderate amount of mucosal hyperenhancement and surrounding fat stranding/fluid, compatible with acute appendicitis. No appendicolith. No bowel obstruction. 10 mm hypodensity within segment III of the liver demonstrates a focus of peripheral hyperenhancement, likely representing hemangioma. Additional hypodensity in the liver is too small to characterize.
